People who got this course at the beginning of their ML journey have no idea how lucky they are. Courses like this are so rare, here you get simple overview what ML engineering is all about in the REAL WORLD. Most of the courses focus on very low level stuff, go in depth of single topic what is huge overkill for most of the use cases at companies. Companies usually need simple but complete solution. No one cares if you can do CNN object detection model but only in Google Colab. This course will save you a lot of time, you won't be asking "how I actually do this, do that", here you have all you need to start working as ML. In fact this course should be first one you do right after understanding Python basics and libraries such as pandas, numpy, scikit, tensorflow (sequential model only) if you want to become MLE fast.
